@startuml LAPS Sequence
!theme plain
autonumber

actor "Employee" as User1
actor "Manager" as User2
boundary ":LeavePortalUI" as View
control ":EmployeeController" as Controller
control ":ManagerController" as Controller2
participant "LeaveService" as Service1
database "LeaveApplicationRepository" as Domain1
database "LeaveEntitlementRepository" as Domain2

== Phase: User Interface Interaction ==
User1 -> View : Fills Leave Application Form

== Phase: Web Request Routing ==
View -> Controller : applyLeave()

== Phase: Business Logic & Validation ==
Controller -> Service1 : applyLeave(application, employee)
Service1 -> Domain1 : save(application)

== Phase: Manager Review ==
User2 -> View: Clicks pending leaves
View -> Controller2 : viewPendingLeaves()
Controller2 -> Service1 : getPendingApplicationsForManager(manager)
Service1 -> Domain1 : findPendingByManager(manager)
Domain1 --> Service1 : List<LeaveApplication>
Service1 --> Controller2 : List<LeaveApplication>
Controller2 --> View : Render Pending Leaves

User2 -> View : Clicks "Review" on a specific leave application
View -> Controller2 : viewLeaveDetail()
Controller2 -> Service1 : findById(id)
Service1 -> Domain1 : findById(id)
Controller2 -> Service1 : getSubordinateLeaveDuringPeriod(manager, startDate, endDate)
Service1 -> Domain1 : findSubordinateLeaveDuringPeriod(manager, startDate, endDate)
Domain1 --> Service1 : List<LeaveApplication>
Service1 --> Controller2 : List<LeaveApplication>
Controller2 --> View : Render Leave Detail

== Phase: Data Persistence (Approval) ==
User2 -> View : Clicks "Approve"
View -> Controller2 : approveLeave()
Controller2 -> Service1 : approveLeave(id, comment, manager)
Service1 -> Domain1 : findById(id)
Service1 -> Domain1 : save(application)
Service1 -> Service1 : deductEntitlement(application, employee)
Service1 -> Domain2 : findByEmployeeAndLeaveTypeAndYear(employee, leaveType, year)
Service1 -> Domain2 : save(ent)
@enduml